dct_title_s: Nova et accurata Descriptio Delphinatus vulgo Dauphiné; Joannes Janssonius excudit.; Nova et accurata descriptio Delphinatvs vulgo Davphiné
dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. Includes a compass rose and the coat of arms of the Dauphin. The title caroutche depicts two winged heads, boughs of fruit, and a face. Was printed in Jansson's Atlas Novus in 1680. From the Jansson Appendix Atlas 1636-1680, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan. 1 map; 36 x 50 cm.
dct_rights_sm: This map is in the public domain.
